1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,120
You dare walk away from me?

2
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:59,320
It's not time for him to know

3
00:03:01,440 --> 00:03:02,800
who you are.

4
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:10,040
No!

5
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:22,879
- Alright.
- Give me the drug.

6
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:25,800
Okay. One moment.

7
00:03:27,040 --> 00:03:29,400
Hey, who's that?

8
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:39,520
A woman.

9
00:03:46,480 --> 00:03:47,640
She's pretty.

10
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:51,680
Why don't we have fun with her?

11
00:03:53,880 --> 00:03:56,360
Then go watch out for me.

12
00:03:59,040 --> 00:04:04,400
I'm gonna take a little trip to heaven
with this angel first.

13
00:04:05,200 --> 00:04:08,120
- Ugh, come on.
- Go.

14
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:33,440
You filthy bastard.

15
00:04:52,200 --> 00:04:56,200
Hey, bro, how was it? You took forever.

16
00:04:58,520 --> 00:05:01,360
I knew it. You're completely out cold.

17
00:05:08,360 --> 00:05:09,600
What happened?

18
00:05:40,320 --> 00:05:42,440
Didn't Mek come with you?

19
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,760
No, he didn't.

20
00:05:49,600 --> 00:05:51,040
Is something wrong?

21
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:57,639
We came to see Ms. Boonsong,

22
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:00,080
but she wasn't home.

23
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:03,440
So we wanted to come pay our respects.

24
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,000
You know Boonsong?

25
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:10,400
No, we don't.

26
00:06:14,440 --> 00:06:16,200
Then just tell me what's on your mind.

27
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:20,080
If I can help,

28
00:06:21,440 --> 00:06:22,920
I will.

29
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:27,919
Do you remember the spirit of a woman

30
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:31,480
followed Dara, so you had to
give her the sacred thread to protect her?

31
00:06:34,240 --> 00:06:35,600
Of course I do.

32
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:40,320
I know

33
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,320
who that woman is now.

34
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,080
Her name is Sarai.

35
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:50,160
She was another wife of my father.

36
00:07:23,400 --> 00:07:25,240
Did you need something from me?

37
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:29,480
Narathon came to see me earlier.

38
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,600
He came to visit?

39
00:07:32,280 --> 00:07:34,000
He's waiting to take care
of some business.

40
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:37,280
I hear he'll be stopping
by the fish farm house.

41
00:07:38,080 --> 00:07:40,120
Then can I go see him?

42
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,360
Do you like him that much?

43
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:48,319
Yes. He's really kind.

44
00:07:48,320 --> 00:07:50,640
I wish I had an older brother like him.

45
00:07:53,240 --> 00:07:55,039
Then you'd better hurry along.

46
00:07:55,040 --> 00:07:56,520
Thank you, Venerable Sir.

47
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,600
Kang,

48
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:13,200
it's time you were where you belong.

49
00:08:15,520 --> 00:08:18,040
I've wronged you far too much.

50
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:36,079
You told Venerable Sir about Sarai

51
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:39,559
because you wanted him
to contact her spirit for you, didn't you?

52
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:44,080
Yes.

53
00:08:46,240 --> 00:08:47,960
I thought he might be able to do it.

54
00:08:56,680 --> 00:08:58,680
He's a very strict monk.

55
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:02,120
He probably doesn't want
to get involved in worldly matters.

56
00:09:06,520 --> 00:09:07,680
I was too impatient.

57
00:09:10,920 --> 00:09:12,200
I really want to know

58
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:15,520
who killed Sarai.

59
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:26,519
Don't worry too much.

60
00:09:26,520 --> 00:09:31,000
Once we meet Ms. Boonsong,
we'll probably learn the truth.

61
00:09:38,240 --> 00:09:39,640
Thon, Kaimook.

62
00:09:40,320 --> 00:09:41,399
- Hello.
- Oh.

63
00:09:41,400 --> 00:09:42,720
What's up, Kang?

64
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:45,479
It's perfect timing that you're here.

65
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:48,959
Mr. Thon and I were just about
to make spaghetti.

66
00:09:48,960 --> 00:09:50,399
Stay and eat with us, okay?

67
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:52,960
I've never had spaghetti before.

68
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:56,919
Then all the more reason to try it.

69
00:09:56,920 --> 00:10:01,280
I guarantee you'll love my cooking.

70
00:10:01,880 --> 00:10:02,720
Exactly.

71
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,120
Even I'm hooked on it.

72
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,919
Let's go to the kitchen.

73
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:14,159
Sure. I'll help you as your assistant.

74
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,320
Okay.

75
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,479
It's me, Mom.

76
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:48,239
Na, you scared me.

77
00:10:48,240 --> 00:10:50,840
- Hello.
- Hello, Da.

78
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,040
Where is Mook?

79
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:57,360
Mook?

80
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,880
Didn't she go out with you?

81
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,359
Go where?

82
00:11:02,360 --> 00:11:04,359
What?

83
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,759
Mook told me she was going with you.

84
00:11:06,760 --> 00:11:09,800
She even said she'd be home late
and told us not to wait for dinner.

85
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,120
That's weird. Why would Mook lie?

86
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:17,240
Where could she have gone?

87
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,680
Could she have gone with Mr. Narathon?

88
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:26,639
Oh, dear.

89
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:29,279
If she really went with Mr. Narathon
and lied about it,

90
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,200
that's even worse.

91
00:11:32,920 --> 00:11:36,879
Listen, Na. Take Da out
for dinner right now.

92
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:39,839
Don't let your father see you yet.

93
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,799
Go on, hurry. I'll call Mook immediately.

94
00:11:41,800 --> 00:11:43,320
- Yes.
- Let's go.

95
00:12:06,640 --> 00:12:09,799
That land originally
belonged to someone named Son.

96
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,639
He mortgaged it to me.

97
00:12:11,640 --> 00:12:13,719
At first, he kept up the payments,

98
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,639
but then one day he disappeared.

99
00:12:15,640 --> 00:12:17,440
Nobody could find him.

100
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:21,320
What did Son do for a living?

101
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:23,559
He was a fishing boat deckhand.

102
00:12:23,560 --> 00:12:26,360
He'd go out to sea for days at a time.

103
00:12:28,560 --> 00:12:30,280
Did he have a family?

104
00:12:30,880 --> 00:12:34,119
He had a wife, but she died giving birth.

105
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:37,920
So Son raised their daughter
by himself until she grew up.

106
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:43,039
Do you know his daughter?

107
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:46,359
Of course. I watched her grow up.

108
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:49,159
But later she disappeared.

109
00:12:49,160 --> 00:12:52,999
People said she'd made
a good life for herself in Bangkok.

110
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:55,519
But that wasn't true.

111
00:12:55,520 --> 00:12:58,039
Later, I saw her
come back with a small child.

112
00:12:58,040 --> 00:13:02,479
She'd probably become someone's mistress
or kept woman.

113
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:05,600
Then she disappeared again,
both her and the child.

114
00:13:06,160 --> 00:13:09,439
No one ever came to reclaim the land,
so I took possession of it

115
00:13:09,440 --> 00:13:11,360
and sold it.

116
00:13:14,600 --> 00:13:17,480
What was Son's daughter's name?

117
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,400
Let me think. It was such a long time ago.

118
00:13:25,600 --> 00:13:26,960
Sarai.

119
00:13:28,080 --> 00:13:29,199
Sarai?

120
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,600
Yes, Sarai.

121
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:47,520
The truth is even worse than I imagined.

122
00:13:48,800 --> 00:13:50,240
How could my dad do that?

123
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:52,920
Sarai had a child with him.

124
00:14:05,520 --> 00:14:07,200
Mr. Phum is calling.

125
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:14,160
Hello. Yes.

126
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,880
Of course. I'd be more than happy to.

127
00:14:20,520 --> 00:14:23,360
In that case, I'll come see you
at the company tomorrow.

128
00:14:25,200 --> 00:14:26,880
Okay. Goodbye.

129
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:32,079
Luck is finally on our side.

130
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:34,760
Mr. Phum wants me
to help with the photo exhibition.

131
00:14:36,680 --> 00:14:38,880
But I don't want you
anywhere near someone like him.

132
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:42,480
- He--
- But this is a good opportunity

133
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,080
for us to investigate everything.

134
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:48,119
But...

135
00:14:48,120 --> 00:14:51,880
If you're worried about me,
then come help me.

136
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:08,079
Oh, Mr. Phum.

137
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:10,039
- Hello.
- Ms. Pat, hello.

138
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:12,160
- Are you here to visit Ms. Pakarang?
- Yes.

139
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:14,559
I was just about to go see her.

140
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:16,799
I stopped by this morning

141
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:19,679
and she didn't look very well,

142
00:15:19,680 --> 00:15:21,560
so I brought her some food.

143
00:15:22,200 --> 00:15:25,440
You're very thoughtful.
Thank you for helping take care of her.

144
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:28,159
Since you're here,

145
00:15:28,160 --> 00:15:31,439
tomorrow, I've scheduled
a meeting with my team at the gallery.

146
00:15:31,440 --> 00:15:33,519
If you're free,
I'd love for you to join us.

147
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,280
Of course. Let me help.

148
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:38,040
Alright. Thank you.

149
00:15:39,560 --> 00:15:40,399
Is it too heavy?

150
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,440
Not at all. Ah, the elevator's here.

151
00:15:47,760 --> 00:15:50,479
You didn't answer your phone all day,
so I came by.

152
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:52,040
Thought you might be seriously ill.

153
00:15:54,760 --> 00:15:56,199
I'm feeling much better now.

154
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:58,320
I went out for a walk
and got some fresh air.

155
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,839
Right. This morning, you looked pale,

156
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:05,159
but now you look completely refreshed.

157
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:08,040
If you didn't tell me,
I'd think you faked it.

158
00:16:12,160 --> 00:16:14,759
I bought all sorts of food.

159
00:16:14,760 --> 00:16:17,319
Rice flour dumplings,

160
00:16:17,320 --> 00:16:19,439
crispy shrimp rolls,

161
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:20,600
Vietnamese fermented pork rolls.

162
00:16:29,080 --> 00:16:31,080
Those are all Mr. Phum's favorite foods.

163
00:16:33,040 --> 00:16:34,240
Really?

164
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:35,840
Yes.

165
00:16:36,800 --> 00:16:38,800
How do you know I like Vietnamese food?

166
00:16:41,440 --> 00:16:42,800
Oh.

167
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:44,680
I like it,

168
00:16:45,280 --> 00:16:47,280
so I thought maybe you would too.

169
00:16:50,240 --> 00:16:52,520
We seem to have
the same tastes quite often.

170
00:16:59,160 --> 00:17:01,239
I'll put them on a plate.

171
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,760
Let me help.

172
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:04,520
No need, Ms. Pat.

173
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:08,838
You can talk with Mr. Phum.
I'll take care of it.

174
00:17:08,839 --> 00:17:10,280
Sure.

175
00:17:11,640 --> 00:17:14,078
Wait, what's that on your shirt?

176
00:17:14,079 --> 00:17:16,400
It looks like blood.

177
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:31,120
Right. Did something happen to you?

178
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:38,120
It's sauce. I must've spilled it
while I was making something to eat.

179
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:43,159
Then why don't you go change first?

180
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:45,839
I won't be able to eat
if I keep looking at it.

181
00:17:45,840 --> 00:17:47,199
It really looks like blood.

182
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,840
I'll take care of these.

183
00:17:52,320 --> 00:17:53,439
Alright.

184
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:56,400
- I'll help you.
- Thank you.

185
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:24,319
- Everything's good.
- And the concept...

186
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:26,800
Oh, there you are.

187
00:19:28,200 --> 00:19:31,720
Mr. Phum and I prepared it together.

188
00:19:33,560 --> 00:19:36,599
I feel bad just sitting here and eating.

189
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,359
Don't overthink.

190
00:19:38,360 --> 00:19:41,239
I barely had a chance to help.
Ms. Pat managed everything.

191
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:42,199
She's truly capable.

192
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,800
She's good at both household chores
and professional work.

193
00:19:55,680 --> 00:19:57,359
Shall we eat?

194
00:19:57,360 --> 00:19:59,479
Good. Let's eat.

195
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,479
Good.

196
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:02,000
Ms. Pat.

197
00:20:02,680 --> 00:20:05,760
Then let me prepare
the first bite for you.

198
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:07,399
Sure.

199
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:10,760
Consider it my way of thanking you
for being so kind to me.

200
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:28,000
Thank you. It must be tasty.

201
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:36,199
This bite is specially prepared for you.

202
00:20:36,200 --> 00:20:37,920
Thank you.

203
00:20:51,640 --> 00:20:53,440
Well? Is it good?

204
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:07,680
What's wrong with her?

205
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:13,640
I have no idea. I'll go check on her.

206
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:36,839
What did you make me eat?
There was blood and worms in it.

207
00:21:36,840 --> 00:21:39,399
Are you feeling sick?

208
00:21:39,400 --> 00:21:42,839
What you spat out were
the side dishes from the Vietnamese rolls.

209
00:21:42,840 --> 00:21:44,800
That's not true. Look--

210
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:59,639
Just now there were worms and blood.

211
00:21:59,640 --> 00:22:02,080
Maybe your eyes
were playing tricks on you.

212
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:05,919
If you happened to be someone
who likes gossiping and slandering others,

213
00:22:05,920 --> 00:22:07,439
I'd think the spirits

214
00:22:07,440 --> 00:22:10,280
were punishing you
and making your mouth rot with worms.

215
00:22:13,760 --> 00:22:17,199
Please wash your hands and mouth.
Mr. Phum is waiting to eat.

216
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:19,520
The food will get cold.

217
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:52,480
You won't eat anymore, Ms. Pat?

218
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:54,640
No.

219
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:56,920
Eat it, Pakarang.

220
00:22:59,160 --> 00:23:00,480
I'm not hungry.

221
00:23:01,720 --> 00:23:05,440
You won't eat and Ms. Pat won't eat.
So I'm the only one eating.

222
00:23:07,840 --> 00:23:11,080
I'm not feeling very well.

223
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,359
Are you alright?

224
00:23:13,360 --> 00:23:15,119
I'm fine.

225
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:18,399
Please continue enjoying your meal.

226
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:20,040
I'll excuse myself now.

227
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:23,319
- I'll walk you out.
- It's fine.

228
00:23:23,320 --> 00:23:25,160
It's only a short distance.

229
00:23:42,800 --> 00:23:44,080
I know

230
00:23:45,920 --> 00:23:47,720
why you've been feeling unwell.

231
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:54,360
You know?

232
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:01,359
The fresh food in the refrigerator,
the ready-made food,

233
00:24:01,360 --> 00:24:04,719
even the food I brought,
you haven't touched any of it.

234
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:08,120
Don't be so considerate of me
that you end up making yourself sick.

235
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:15,200
I'm worried about you.

236
00:24:30,120 --> 00:24:31,400
And what about me?

237
00:24:34,200 --> 00:24:35,760
Have you ever worried about me?

238
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:38,720
Have you ever missed me?

239
00:24:42,280 --> 00:24:43,800
You're so cruel, Mr. Phum.

240
00:24:50,200 --> 00:24:52,600
You're crying...

241
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:56,040
I'm just happy

242
00:24:57,440 --> 00:24:58,920
that you care about me.

243
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:08,600
Then promise me something.

244
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:12,440
From now on, don't hesitate
to eat any of that food anymore.

245
00:25:15,480 --> 00:25:16,520
Okay.

246
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:21,600
I need to wash my face.

247
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:43,400
It's not time yet.

248
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,040
Thank you for the ride.

249
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,799
You should head back
before my father sees you.

250
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:19,559
See you tomorrow.

251
00:26:19,560 --> 00:26:20,640
See you.

252
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:24,320
Dad.

253
00:26:40,640 --> 00:26:41,840
Why did you lie?

254
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:47,960
I'm sorry, Dad. I'm sorry, Mom.

255
00:26:53,040 --> 00:26:54,760
It's my fault.

256
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:57,159
I invited Kaimook out.

257
00:26:57,160 --> 00:26:59,560
Then why didn't you
ask my permission directly?

258
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:04,040
Sneaking around like this
shows no respect for her elders.

259
00:27:05,080 --> 00:27:07,879
I was afraid you wouldn't allow it,

260
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:10,760
so I suggested that Kaimook lie.

261
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,280
Mr. Narathon...

262
00:27:17,960 --> 00:27:20,519
I apologize.

263
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:21,920
I apologize to both of you.

264
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,040
Where did you take my daughter?

265
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:33,200
We went to watch a movie

266
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:35,720
and then had dinner.

267
00:27:37,960 --> 00:27:39,520
You can't fool me.

268
00:27:41,440 --> 00:27:44,240
If it were only that,
my daughter wouldn't have needed to lie.

269
00:27:45,600 --> 00:27:47,040
I know my daughter.

270
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,160
I'll give you one more chance.

271
00:27:51,680 --> 00:27:55,120
If you're still planning to lie to me,
you will never see Kaimook again.

272
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:10,800
Fine. If you're not going to talk,

273
00:28:11,640 --> 00:28:12,920
then leave.

274
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,400
Wait, Dad.

275
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:22,040
Mr. Narathon really did lie.

276
00:28:22,640 --> 00:28:23,600
Kaimook.

277
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:31,400
But he lied
because he was trying to help me.

278
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:34,079
What do you mean?

279
00:28:34,080 --> 00:28:37,120
I went to help Mr. Phum
with the photo exhibition

280
00:28:37,680 --> 00:28:40,600
that's raising funds
for a coral restoration project.

281
00:28:41,480 --> 00:28:43,520
I wanted to contribute.

282
00:28:44,480 --> 00:28:46,160
I wanted to be part of it.

283
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:51,560
Most of the photographs were taken by me.

284
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:57,360
So I was afraid to ask your permission

285
00:28:58,640 --> 00:29:01,240
because I thought you'd never agree.

286
00:29:09,160 --> 00:29:12,720
Next time, don't assume things
and drag someone else into trouble.

287
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:16,000
I'm sorry.

288
00:29:23,280 --> 00:29:24,960
You may have wanted to help Kaimook,

289
00:29:26,360 --> 00:29:30,080
but lying never improves anything.

290
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:33,960
The thing I hate most is dishonesty.

291
00:29:40,920 --> 00:29:42,520
But this time, I'll let it slide.

292
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:44,800
If it happens again,

293
00:29:45,560 --> 00:29:47,240
I won't be so considerate.

294
00:29:47,880 --> 00:29:49,159
I'm sorry.

295
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:52,320
And thank you
for giving me another chance.

296
00:29:54,160 --> 00:29:58,240
In that case, I'd better get going.

297
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:01,360
Goodbye.

298
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,400
Good morning.

299
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:32,720
Mr. Narathon...

300
00:30:37,920 --> 00:30:40,200
You know me?

301
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:45,200
Oh, Kaimook.

302
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:47,159
Mr. Phum.

303
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:48,840
- Hello.
- Hello.

304
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,680
I didn't expect to see you here.

305
00:30:52,920 --> 00:30:54,560
I came with Kaimook.

306
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,280
I'm worried about her safety.

307
00:30:58,000 --> 00:30:58,799
You can rest easy.

308
00:30:58,800 --> 00:31:02,159
There are CCTV cameras everywhere,
including my office.

309
00:31:02,160 --> 00:31:05,240
And more importantly,
the CCTV here has never once broken down.

310
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,559
Kaimook, this way, please.

311
00:31:09,560 --> 00:31:12,119
Pakarang, please bring orange juice.

312
00:31:12,120 --> 00:31:13,200
Yes.

313
00:31:17,360 --> 00:31:18,240
I'll wait outside.

314
00:31:38,720 --> 00:31:39,880
Pakarang?

315
00:31:54,320 --> 00:31:55,600
I remember you now.

316
00:31:59,880 --> 00:32:03,360
You're the woman my father brought
to stay at the condo.

317
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:12,920
You know me?

318
00:32:14,800 --> 00:32:16,960
I saw you at the hospital.

319
00:32:17,600 --> 00:32:19,519
But I learned your name

320
00:32:19,520 --> 00:32:21,440
from my father's wife.

321
00:32:22,480 --> 00:32:24,760
Oh, I see.

322
00:32:28,960 --> 00:32:30,160
Don't you feel anything?

323
00:32:31,960 --> 00:32:33,520
Feel what?

324
00:32:34,120 --> 00:32:38,080
About living with a man
who already has a wife.

325
00:32:47,680 --> 00:32:49,960
I know it's none of my business.

326
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:54,760
I just want to warn you.
My father is no ordinary man.

327
00:33:00,880 --> 00:33:02,040
Be careful.

328
00:33:06,280 --> 00:33:08,160
Thank you, Mr. Narathon.

329
00:33:09,040 --> 00:33:10,600
You're still as kind as ever.

330
00:33:12,800 --> 00:33:14,320
But don't worry.

331
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,240
I won't let myself
be fooled a second time.

332
00:33:35,680 --> 00:33:37,240
Your orange juice.

333
00:33:41,040 --> 00:33:44,040
How did you know I like
lime squeezed into my orange juice?

334
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:53,919
I'm glad you understand my intention
and agreed to help.

335
00:33:53,920 --> 00:33:55,240
Thank you very much.

336
00:33:56,680 --> 00:33:59,199
I'm the one
who should thank you, Mr. Phum.

337
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:01,359
If everyone wanted to help conserve

338
00:34:01,360 --> 00:34:04,519
and restore natural resources
the way you do,

339
00:34:04,520 --> 00:34:07,200
nature would stay with us forever.

340
00:34:08,239 --> 00:34:10,359
Then shall we go to the gallery now?

341
00:34:10,360 --> 00:34:12,719
You'll get to meet Ms. Pat too.

342
00:34:13,320 --> 00:34:14,679
Of course.

343
00:34:21,040 --> 00:34:21,920
Well.

344
00:34:25,159 --> 00:34:26,280
Why won't you answer?

345
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:33,000
- It's probably just a coincidence.
- That's not true.

346
00:34:34,800 --> 00:34:37,880
There's only one woman
who knew I drank orange juice with lime.

347
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:42,600
Who is that?

348
00:34:45,120 --> 00:34:47,239
Don't answer my question
with another question.

349
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:53,080
When we came in, you called my name

350
00:34:54,639 --> 00:34:56,719
even though you've never met me before.

351
00:34:58,600 --> 00:34:59,760
Who are you really?

352
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:07,160
You're Mr. Phum's son.
Why wouldn't I know you?

353
00:35:10,120 --> 00:35:11,200
And the orange juice?

354
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:18,200
Well.

355
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:23,400
I already told you.
It must be a coincidence.

356
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:27,640
I happen to like orange juice
with a little lime too.

357
00:35:28,320 --> 00:35:31,359
I even put lime in iced black tea.

358
00:35:31,360 --> 00:35:33,280
So I must have put it
in yours without thinking.

359
00:35:34,600 --> 00:35:37,440
Then why didn't you put lime
in the other two glasses?

360
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:57,720
Why won't you answer.

361
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:02,240
I'm asking you.

362
00:36:10,400 --> 00:36:11,520
Narathon.

363
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,040
What are you doing?

364
00:36:22,960 --> 00:36:26,600
Mr. Narathon was going
to carry the tray for me.

365
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:34,040
I'm going to the gallery. Go get ready.

366
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:35,480
Yes.

367
00:36:48,240 --> 00:36:50,999
I'm going to the restroom first.

368
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,360
You can wait by the car.
I'll follow you soon.

369
00:37:00,960 --> 00:37:02,640
I want to talk to you.

370
00:37:04,560 --> 00:37:06,360
But I have nothing to say to you.

371
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,400
Narathon.

372
00:37:25,160 --> 00:37:26,160
Thon.

373
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,800
Pakarang is a good person.

374
00:37:32,600 --> 00:37:36,440
I'm asking you,
not to say anything that will hurt her.

375
00:37:39,640 --> 00:37:41,400
I'm so proud

376
00:37:42,680 --> 00:37:44,560
to have such a gentleman for a father.

377
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:47,239
But be careful.

378
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:50,720
The mask you're wearing
is about to fall off.

379
00:37:51,920 --> 00:37:53,359
What are you imagining now?

380
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:55,480
I hope what I'm imagining

381
00:37:56,520 --> 00:37:58,120
is wrong.

382
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:02,039
Can you stop speaking
in riddles and insinuations?

383
00:38:02,040 --> 00:38:04,000
Just say it directly. I'm sick of this.

384
00:38:12,400 --> 00:38:15,880
If you weren't my son, I would've
punched you several times already.

385
00:38:42,760 --> 00:38:46,120
Mr. Narathon, try this orange juice.
It's super sweet.

386
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:58,559
Too sweet. I don't like it.

387
00:38:58,560 --> 00:39:01,399
But orange juice is very good for you.

388
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:02,959
It has vitamin C too.

389
00:39:02,960 --> 00:39:04,680
I read that in a book.

390
00:39:16,920 --> 00:39:18,320
Try it.

391
00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:31,080
It's good.

392
00:39:34,840 --> 00:39:36,119
Then from now on,

393
00:39:36,120 --> 00:39:38,959
I'll make orange juice
this way just for you.

394
00:39:38,960 --> 00:39:41,040
It'll be my way of thanking you
for tutoring me.

395
00:39:42,560 --> 00:39:43,560
Thank you.

396
00:39:51,480 --> 00:39:53,920
You still remember these things.

397
00:40:10,800 --> 00:40:12,080
Pakarang.

398
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:17,680
Did Narathon say something to you?

399
00:40:20,680 --> 00:40:21,720
No.

400
00:40:23,560 --> 00:40:25,360
He must have misunderstood
our relationship.

401
00:40:26,040 --> 00:40:29,120
If he said or did anything hurtful,

402
00:40:29,760 --> 00:40:31,680
then I apologize on his behalf.

403
00:40:34,600 --> 00:40:39,039
Mr. Narathon didn't say
or do anything wrong to me.

404
00:40:39,040 --> 00:40:40,520
You don't need to worry.

405
00:40:42,680 --> 00:40:46,280
I think you're very lucky
to have a son like him.

406
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:53,680
Shall we go?

407
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:55,720
Yes.

408
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:12,880
Don't you want to ask me anything?

409
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:15,520
No.

410
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,200
But I want to explain.

411
00:41:20,720 --> 00:41:22,040
No need.

412
00:41:25,200 --> 00:41:28,360
Pakarang isn't just a secretary.

413
00:41:30,800 --> 00:41:32,720
She's my father's new woman.

414
00:41:34,080 --> 00:41:37,679
I didn't want her to end up
with the same fate as Sarai, so...

415
00:41:37,680 --> 00:41:39,080
I know.

416
00:41:56,720 --> 00:41:58,799
- Uh, you...
- Don't think too much about it.

417
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:01,720
Mr. Narathon only came
to warn me about Mr. Phum.

418
00:42:03,160 --> 00:42:06,800
You should stay away from Mr. Phum too.

419
00:42:08,320 --> 00:42:10,200
What do you mean?

420
00:42:11,880 --> 00:42:13,960
For now, that's all I can tell you.

421
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:16,320
One day, you'll understand.

422
00:42:17,960 --> 00:42:20,400
Thank you very much, Ms. Kaimook.

423
00:42:21,160 --> 00:42:24,800
If it weren't for you,
I wouldn't be here today.

424
00:42:40,080 --> 00:42:42,920
Ms. Pakarang talked
as if she'd known me before.

425
00:42:44,200 --> 00:42:45,800
I felt the same way.

426
00:42:48,040 --> 00:42:52,080
But I'm sure I've never met her.

427
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:57,360
The way she talks
and behaves reminds me of...

428
00:42:59,000 --> 00:43:00,240
Who?

429
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:03,080
Sarai.

430
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:08,200
Could she be related to Sarai?

431
00:43:09,360 --> 00:43:10,640
Are you saying

432
00:43:12,040 --> 00:43:17,719
she got close to my father to investigate
Sarai's death,

433
00:43:17,720 --> 00:43:19,280
just like we are?

434
00:43:21,560 --> 00:43:23,320
I'm not sure.

435
00:43:24,640 --> 00:43:27,680
But she doesn't seem to like your father.

436
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:31,360
So why would she agree to become...

437
00:43:32,400 --> 00:43:36,800
Mr. Phum's woman
unless she wants something?

438
00:43:41,280 --> 00:43:44,440
I think we should keep
a close eye on this woman.

439
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:46,840
Maybe,

440
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:51,000
we might discover the truth
sooner than we expected.

441
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:13,080
Is that you, Sarai?

442
00:44:17,800 --> 00:44:19,200
You must die!

443
00:44:19,800 --> 00:44:20,880
Sarai!

444
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:57,560
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
